"P562939599" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Discarded Picket Sign</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You find an abandoned picket sign whilst fighting crime. You pick it up and read it over...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>The petition sign reads: 'Raise the Wages, or Raze the Docks!' You remember hearing that the local Dockworkers' Union was protesting pay rates and working conditions as of late. Looking into it further, it turns out that the Dockworkers' Union has hired out large groups of Scapyarders from Cage Consortium to do more of their manual work!<br><br>While this is all legal, it certainly reeks, given the shady practices in the past by Cage.<br><br> The wording of this sign looks like the protest is beginning to get rather heated - which will be bad, considering most of the Scrapyarders are former ex-cons!</scale></font></color><br><br>If the rhetoric continues to build, the protests could result in violence.  It may be time for someone to talk to the protest leaders to calm them down before someone gets hurt.<br><br>It's possible that they're already on verge of a riot. What good will words do when actions can get things done faster? Beating the rioters into a pulp is definitely one way of calming them down."
// Answer Text :
"P1456515668" "HERO: Talk down the protest leaders before it becomes a riot."
// Answer Text :
"P1789271218" "VIGILANTE: These protesters are getting dangerous. Put them down!"
// Page Rogue Text :
"P3666025264" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Discarded Picket Sign</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You find an abandoned picket sign whilst fighting crime. You pick it up and read it over...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>The petition sign reads: 'Raise the Wages, or Raze the Docks!'. You remember hearing that the local Dockworkers' Union was protesting pay rates and working conditions as of late. Looking into it further, it turns out that the Dockworkers' Union has hired out large groups of Scapyarders from Cage Consortium to do more of their manual work!<br><br>While this is all legal, it certainly reeks, given the shady practices in the past by Cage.<br><br> The wording of this sign looks like the protest is beginning to get rather heated - which will be bad, considering most of the Scrapyarders are former ex-cons!</scale></font></color><br><br>You'd think that these Scrapyarders would be happy that they're not working in the Pit anymore. The fact that they're demanding higher wages show they're getting a little <i>too</i> comfortable with their new situation. However, having them riot and get out of control will just further the idea that people from the Rogue Isles can't be trusted - and given that you just happen to be someone coming over from the Isles, it might be best to try to garner the trust of the people here in Paragon."
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


